							</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>This is really very naive:<br />
&#8220;Not sure if this could feasibly be used for malicious purposes really, &#8221;</p>
<p>You might have picked up in the last 20 years that the main big brother thread is in the &#8220;Big Data&#8221; thing and combining stuff from multiple sources. You take a few stills from a camera to identify persons and then follow them for the rest of the day through the whole building with techniques like this. People are also creatures of habit. If a person is sitting at a particular desk for some hours, it&#8217;s pretty obvious which employee it is and you can start logging time at the coffee machine, talks with colleagues in the hallway and toilet breaks.</p>
